Anyone interested in pet facial recognition?
text:
Hey everyone,

I own a start up in the pet tech space, and it's growing pretty quickly. We've onboarded >100k paying users within ~1 year of operating (7 fig ARR). It's a small team with only one engineer currently (hey, that's me!).

Our team is super passionate about pets, so we're willing to invest a lot of our own capital into research to fix the issue of missing pets. That being said, we're really eager to add a pet facial (maybe body too?) recognition feature to our platform.

We'll roll this out to vet partners across the world and slowly release it to regular users too. Our biggest strength is advertising, so we're confident we could get this to 1M+ users in a year.

If you're interested in developing ethical AI and have a love for pets, this might be a great opportunity for you!

If you're interested, please comment your email below, and I'll reach out :)
